                "show_points": true,
                "tips_en": "<ul><li>Stage I: disease is located in a single region, usually one lymph node and the surrounding area.</li><li>Stage II: disease is located in two separate regions, an affected lymph node or organ and a second affected area. Both affected areas are confined to one side of the diaphragm. </li><li>Stage III: disease involves both sides of the diaphragm, including one organ or area near the lymph nodes or the spleen.</li><li>Stage IV: diffuse or disseminated involvement of one or more extranodal organs, with or without associated lymph node involvement.</li></ul><p>See <a href=\"#evidence\">Evidence</a> for stage diagram.",
